e deterministic keyword score. Only real LLM inference exposes whether the actual explanation genuinely aligns with the score, making Agentic the minimum level to catch real semantic-mismatch failures.","test_description":"Agentic test that calls the full service pipeline with real LLM inference on multiple reviews across sentiment categories (clearly positive, clearly negative, and borderline/neutral reviews). Verify: (1) the response contains both the sentiment score and explanation, and (2) the explanation's sentiment direction and framing match the sentiment score classification (e.g., if score is negative, explanation should convey dissatisfaction or problems, not satisfaction).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0,"Agentic":0.6,"Workflow":0.1}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13565,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13565},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d3d57c7a-20da-4062-a0f2-badd26ed1790","uuid":"469f5498-f873-4fb7-b927-c4def87d505c"}
